IRS990.Desc: SINCE 1989, THE COASTAL CONSERVATION LEAGUE HAS BEEN PROTECTING THE SOUTH CAROLINA COASTAL PLAIN-ITS NATURAL LANDSCAPES, ABUNDANT WILDLIFE, CLEAN WATER, AND QUALITY OF LIFE-BY WORKING WITH CITIZENS AND GOVERNMENT ON COMPREHENSIVE SOLUTIONS TO ENVIRONMENTAL CHALLENGES. OUR STAFF WORKS THROUGH FOUR MAIN PROGRAM AREAS: LAND & COMMUNITIES; FOOD & AGRICULTURE; AIR, WATER, & PUBLIC HEALTH; AND ENERGY. DURING 2015, WE HAD MANY ACCOMPLISHMENTS AND MOVED MANY PROJECTS FORWARD. OUR WORK AT THE LEGISLATURE AND IN CITY AND COUNTY COUNCILS OFTEN TAKES YEARS, AND SOMETIMES DECADES. BELOW ARE SOME HIGHLIGHTS FROM 2015 BY PROGRAM AREA: FOOD & AGRICULTURE: GROWFOOD CAROLINA, OUR FOOD HUB, EXCEEDED THEIR 2015 SALES GOAL, EXPANDING OUR LOCAL FOOD SUPPLY RADIUS TO THE ENTIRE STATE. INVENTORY NOW INCLUDES FRUIT, VEGETABLES, NUTS, GRAINS, DAIRY, EGGS, AND CANOLA OIL.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: ENERGY: THROUGH OUTREACH AND EDUCATION OF ELECTED OFFICIALS, THE CONSERVATION LEAGUE PLAYED AN INTEGRAL ROLE IN SUPPORTING THE PASSAGE OF TWENTY-FOUR (24) OFFICIAL RESOLUTIONS OPPOSING OFFSHORE OIL AND GAS EXPLORATION AND DEVELOPMENT IN THE ATLANTIC. EVERY COASTAL MUNICIPALITY FROM NORTH MYRTLE BEACH TO HILTON HEAD IS INCLUDED IN THIS LIST. IN JULY, THE CONSERVATION LEAGUE CO-HOSTED AN ANTI-OFFSHORE DRILLING EVENT IN MOUNT PLEASANT FEATURING COMMENTS FROM SC SEN. CHIP CAMPSEN AND U.S. REP. MARK SANFORD, TO A CROWD OF MORE THAN 200 PEOPLE. AS A RESULT OF PUBLIC PRESSURE, PRESIDENT OBAMA AGREED TO PROHIBIT OFFSHORE DRILLING ALONG THE ENTIRE EASTERN SEABOARD. GOVERNOR HALEY APPOINTED CONSERVATION LEAGUE STAFF TO AN OFFSHORE ENERGY ADVISORY COMMITTEE THAT WILL BEGIN MEETING NEXT YEAR.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: LAND & COMMUNITIES: WORKING WITH MEMBERS OF THE COMMUNITY, WE SUCCESSFULLY THWARTED EFFORTS TO ADD MORE COMMERCIAL DEVELOPMENT TO THE ASHLEY RIVER HISTORIC DISTRICT. FURTHER, DORCHESTER COUNTY PLANNING COMMISSION IS NOW CONSIDERING CHANGES THAT TIGHTEN REGULATIONS FOR FUTURE COMMERCIAL DEVELOPMENT NEAR THE DISTRICT. THROUGH A COLLABORATIVE APPROACH INVOLVING INDUSTRY AND CONSERVATION INTERESTS, THE COASTAL CONSERVATION LEAGUE WORKED ON AN AGREEMENT WITH VOLVO WHICH WILL RESULT IN THE RESTORATION AND PROTECTION OF 2,458 ACRES OF LAND CRITICAL TO PROTECTING ONE OF SOUTH CAROLINA'S NATURAL TREASURES, FOUR HOLE SWAMP. WE WILL CONTINUE TO WORK WITH OUR PARTNERS TO ENCOURAGE AND LEAD THIS TYPE OF LANDSCAPE-SCALE MITIGATION IN THE FUTURE.

ProgSrvcAccomActyOtherGrp.Desc: AIR, WATER & PUBLIC HEALTH: WE WORKED WITH CHARLESTON COUNTY TO SET TIMELINE TO RETROFIT A LANE ON THE ASHLEY RIVER BRIDGE FOR USE BY PEOPLE WALKING AND BIKING. AT A PUBLIC INFORMATION SESSION, THE MAJORITY OF THE 400 ATTENDEES WERE IN FAVOR OF THE LANE CONVERSION, AND THE EXCITEMENT WAS PALPABLE. CHARLESTON COUNTY WILL "TEST" THE LANE CONVERSION IN THE MONTHS TO COME. IN ADDITION, CONSERVATION LEAGUE STAFF HAS WORKED FOR MONTHS TO REVIVE THE SHELVED JAMES ISLAND CONNECTOR RETROFIT STUDY, BOTH WITH THE PUBLIC AND CITY COUNCIL. THESE EFFORTS AND CONSEQUENT NEW INQUIRIES RESULTED IN A POSITIVE EDITORIAL FROM THE POST AND COURIER SUPPORTING BOTH THE ASHLEY RIVER BRIDGE AND THE JAMES ISLAND CONNECTOR RETROFITS FOR PEOPLE ON BIKES. WE ALSO WORKED WITH PARTNERS AND CITIZEN GROUPS TO PASS THE FIRST PLASTIC BAG BAN IN THE STATE ON ISLE OF PALMS.

A COPY OF THE FORM 990 WAS PROVIDED TO ALL BOARD MEMBERS AFTER REVIEWED BY MANAGEMENT. PRIOR TO FILING, THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS WERE GIVEN 10 DAYS IN WHICH TO PRESENT QUESTIONS AND/OR COMMENTS ABOUT THE FORM. ONCE THESE COMMENTS ARE ADDRESSED, THE FORM 990 IS FILED IN ACCORDANCE WITH REQUIREMENTS.
THE CONFLICT POLICY IS REVIEWED ANNUALLY AND BOARD IF DIRECTORS MEMBERS MUST DISCLOSE ANY POTENTIAL CONFLICTS ANNUALLY AS WELL AS WHEN OR IF THEY ARISE DURING THE YEAR.
THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS CONDUCTS THE ANNUAL PERFORMANCE REVIEW FOR THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR AND APPROVES HIS/HER SALARY.

THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR APPROVES THE SALARY OF TOP MANAGEMENT AND KEY EMPLOYEES DURING THE BUDGETING PROCESS. THE BUDGET IS REVIEWED BY THE FINANCE COMMITTEE AND VOTED ON AND APPROVED BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS.

THE ORGANIZATION MAKES ITS FORM 990 AVAILABLE FOR PUBLIC INSPECTION UPON REQUEST AT ITS CORPORATE OFFICES. THE FORMS ARE ALSO AVAILABLE TO REGISTERED MEMBERS AT HTTP://WWW.CHARITYNAVIGATOR.ORG OR HTTP://WWW.GUIDESTAR.ORG.
THE ORGANIZATION MAKES THESE DOCUMENTS AVAILABLE UPON PUBLIC REQUEST AT ITS CORPORATE OFFICES.
